claim.claim-text:
1. An optical fiber connector, comprising:
a sheath comprising a first recess formed therein and a pole;
a coupling portion detachably received in the first recess of the sheath, the coupling portion comprising a first end surface having a plurality of lenses arranged therein, and a groove defined in a center portion of the first end surface, and an opposing second end surface having a plurality of optical fiber holes formed therein and aligned with the respective lenses; and
a plurality of spring members arranged between the second end surface and an inner surface of the sheath in the first recess, one end of each of the spring members abutting against the second end surface, and an opposite end of each of the spring members abutting against the inner surface of the sheath in the first recess;
wherein the pole slidably engages in the groove.
